      <body>
         <entry xml:id="anqliton-dlgenr"
                xml:lang="en"
                type="mainEntry"
                prev="#onqos-dlgenr"
                next="#anqlimon-dlgenr"
                source="Genesis Rabbah">
            <form type="lemma" opt="false">
               <orth type="lemma" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false" select="true">אנקליטון</orth>
               <orth type="transliteration" xml:lang="fjb" opt="false">ʾnqlyṭwn</orth>
               <pron notation="rabbinic" opt="false">anqliṭon</pron>
               <gramGrp opt="false">
                  <gram type="pos" opt="false">noun</gram>
                  <gram type="gen" opt="false">m.</gram>
               </gramGrp>
               <form type="variant" source="Ox1 V" opt="false">
                  <orth type="variant" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false">אנקלימון</orth>
               </form>
               <form type="variant" source="Ox1" opt="false">
                  <orth type="variant" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false">אנקליטין</orth>
               </form>
               <form type="variant" source="K" opt="false">
                  <orth type="variant" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false">סנקליטון</orth>
               </form>
               <form type="variant" source="Vat1" opt="false">
                  <orth type="variant" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false">אנקריטיריון</orth>
               </form>
               <form type="variant" source="49,9 second occurrence - K V" opt="false">
                  <orth type="variant" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false">אנקליטין</orth>
               </form>
            </form>
            <sense xml:id="anqliton-dlgenr-1" opt="false">
               <usg type="domain" opt="false">law</usg>
               <usg type="socioCultural" norm="borrowing" opt="false">cultural borrowing</usg>
               <usg type="normativity" opt="false">standard</usg>
               <usg type="meaningType" opt="false">lit.</usg>
               <usg type="frequency" opt="false"/>
               <usg type="geographic" opt="false"/>
               <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en" subtype="sense">
                  <quote>appeal [to higher authority]</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="translationEquivalent" xml:lang="la">
                  <quote>libelli apellatori</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="translationEquivalent" xml:lang="grc">
                  <usg opt="false">
                     <lang opt="false">Medieval Greek+</lang>
                  </usg>
                  <quote>ἔκκλητον / ἔγκλητον</quote>
               </cit>
               <lbl opt="false">For spelling cf. Sperber</lbl>
               <cit type="example">
                  <quote>
                     אמר ר' יהודה בר' סימון בשר ודם תולין לו אנקליטון מדוכס לאיפרכוס מאיפרכוס לאיסטרטלטיס ואת בשביל שאין לך מי יתלה לך אנקליטון אנקליטין לא תעשה משפט
         </quote>
                  <bibl default="false" status="draft">
                     <ref type="witness">49,9</ref>
                     <ref type="witness">II 510: 4; 511: 1</ref>
                  </bibl>
                  <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">איסטרטלטיס</ref>
                  <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa" target="eparkhos.html">איפרכוס</ref>
                  <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">דוכס</ref>
                  <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa" target="anqlimon.html">אנקלימון</ref>
                  <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">אנקריטיריון</ref>
                  <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                     <quote>
                        R. Yehuda be-R. Simon said: (Abraham pleaded thus:) ‘Even in the case of a human judge, an appeal can be made from the commander to the prefect and from the prefect to the governor; but you, because no appeal can be made from your judgment, will you not do justly? (cf. Freedman / Simon I 429)
            </quote>
                  </cit>
                  <note anchored="true">=
            <bibl type="ancient" default="false" status="draft">Yalq 83 [25d: 35,36]</bibl>
                  </note>
               </cit>
            </sense>
            <etym type="borrowing" opt="false">
               <lbl opt="false">source language (in this particular sense)</lbl>
               <lang opt="false">Medieval Greek</lang>
               <cit type="etymon" xml:lang="grc">
                  <xr type="related" opt="false">
                     <lbl opt="false">Cf. LBG</lbl>
                     <ref target="http://stephanus.tlg.uci.edu/Iris/indiv/lexica.jsp#qid=120645&amp;ql=E)%2FGKLHTOS%2C%20-ON&amp;q=%E1%BC%94%CE%B3%CE%BA%CE%BB%CE%B7%CF%84%CE%BF%CF%82%2C%20%E2%80%91%CE%BF%CE%BD&amp;usr_input=greek&amp;searchescs=N"
                          type="entry">ἔγκλητος (δίκη)</ref>
                  </xr>
               </cit>
            </etym>
            <note anchored="true">
               Cf. Sperber for other sources. The meaning “liability to charge, chargeable situation” (as in 
      <bibl type="ancient" default="false" status="draft">DtnR 2,29</bibl>) is not attested in GenR (cf. Sperber). The reading <term xml:lang="jpa">סנקליטון</term> (in K) “seems to be a case of prosthetic sigma” (Sperber). Vat 1 represents an independent version of this passage (cf.
      <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">אנקריטיריון</ref>). Cf.
      <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Krauss, LW II 76a</bibl>.
      <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">AC I 159a</bibl>: Gr. <term xml:lang="grc">ἀνακλήσις</term>;
      <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Levy I 114b</bibl>
               <term xml:lang="grc">ἀνακλετόν</term>. Cf.
      <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa" target="anqlimon.html">אנקלימון</ref>
            </note>
            <ref type="bibliography">
               <bibl default="false" status="draft">
                  <title>Sperber (1984)</title>
                  <citedRange>48-49 and 234</citedRange>
               </bibl>
            </ref>
         </entry>
      </body>
